Varnamala: The Sanskrit alphabet, including vowels, consonants, and diacritics.
Matras: Vowel sounds and their representation in writing.
Sandhi: The rules governing the combination of sounds at word junctions.
Samasa: Compound words and their formation.
Basic Grammar: Nouns, pronouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, and their declensions and conjugations.
Simple Sentences: Constructing basic sentences using the learned grammar.
Basic Vocabulary: Common words related to daily life, nature, and culture.